'3:6': [
{sup:"1a", word:"God", vrefs:"Gen. 28:13; Exo. 4:5; 1&nbsp;Kings 18:36; Matt. 22:32; Mark 12:26; Luke 20:37", lines:["The revelation of God&rsquo;s name in this chapter (vv. {Exo3:6|6}, {Exo3:14|14}-{Exo3:16|16}, {Exo3:18|18}) was actually the revelation of God Himself. By such a revelation Moses came to know the One who was calling and sending him to carry out His commission. The divine title in this verse indicates that God is the covenanting God ({Exo2:24|2:24}) and also implies that He is the God of resurrection ({Mat22:31|Matt. 22:31}-{Mat22:32|32} and {Mat22:32^1|note}; {Act3:13|Acts 3:13}). Furthermore, that God is the God of three persons (cf. {Exo3:15|v. 15}) implies that He is the Triune God&mdash;the Father, the Son, and the Spirit ({Mat28:19|Matt. 28:19}). See {Gen12:1^1P2|note 1<sup>1</sup>, par. 2}, in {Gen12|Gen. 12}."]},
],
