'6:1': [
{sup:1, word:"Jehovah", lines:["After Moses expressed his discouragement and bewilderment to the Lord ({Exo5:22|5:22}-{Exo5:23|23}), Jehovah God came in to reconfirm His name and His covenant (vv. {Exo6:1|1}-{Exo6:8|8}). He also gave Moses further training concerning six matters: (1) God&rsquo;s word of assurance (vv. {Exo6:1|1}, {Exo6:6|6}-{Exo6:8|8}, {Exo6:26|26}; {Exo7:4|7:4}-{Exo7:5|5}); (2) the unbelief of the children of Israel (vv. {Exo6:9|9}, {Exo6:12|12}); (3) Pharaoh&rsquo;s stubbornness ({Exo7:3|7:3}-{Exo7:4|4}); (4) Moses&rsquo; natural concept in cleaving to his uncircumcised lips (vv. {Exo6:12|12}, {Exo6:30|30}); (5) God&rsquo;s ordaining of Moses to bring the children of Israel out of Egypt (vv. {Exo6:26|26}-{Exo6:29|29}); and (6) God&rsquo;s strong hand and His great acts of judgment ({Exo7:4|7:4}), which back up His name, His covenant, and His word of assurance."]},
{sup:"a", word:"mighty", vrefs:"Exo. 3:19; 13:3, 9"},
{sup:"b", word:"drive", vrefs:"Exo. 12:33"},
],
