'9:8': [
{sup:1, word:"ashes", lines:["At the end of the fifth plague all the resources of Egypt had been judged by God. Nevertheless, the ashes, the remainder of things burned, still had to be dealt with. This indicates that anything that remains of our fallen life must be judged by God. When the ashes were sprinkled into the air by Moses and Aaron, they became dust that caused boils. In the eyes of God, everything related to the Egyptian living, the living of the world, must be exposed and judged thoroughly. Even the &ldquo;ashes,&rdquo; the remains of sinful things, must be judged. Nothing of the life of the world should remain."]},
],
